# Telnyx-Abacus Chat Architecture

- Use Telnyx as the communication layer for chat UI, session transport, and real-time delivery.
- Use Abacus as the reasoning layer for text generation and conversational intelligence.
- For Telnyx widget-driven chat that should use platform intelligence, route requests through `apps/tenant/app/api/webhooks/telnyx/assistant-proxy/route.ts`.

# Session and Tenant Traceability

- Preserve Telnyx `conversation_id` across requests and store it as `provider_conversation_id` for conversation continuity.
- Pass tenant-aware metadata for observability (for example `telnyx_proxy_brain`, `telnyx_conversation_id`) so events can be traced per tenant.
- Keep transport concerns (Telnyx IDs/events) separate from LLM response concerns (Abacus content/usage).

# Verification

- To prove responses come from Abacus (not Telnyx native LLM): see `docs/TELNYX_ABACUS_VERIFICATION.md` (observability logs, fingerprint prefix `ABACUS_RESPONSE_PREFIX`, invalid-key test, checklist).

# Security Requirements

- Never expose `ABACUS_API_KEY` in client code, widget snippets, or browser-visible payloads.
- Resolve provider credentials only on trusted server paths (provider drivers, webhook routes, server actions).
